# Vault Password File Example
# 
# This file should contain a single line with the password used to encrypt/decrypt
# the Ansible vault files (ansible/group_vars/all/vault.yml)
#
# TO USE:
# 1. Copy this file to .vault_password_file (which is gitignored)
# 2. Add your actual password on line 1 (replace the example)
# 3. Ensure correct permissions: chmod 600 .vault_password_file
# 4. Update ansible.cfg to reference this file
#
# SECURITY NOTES:
# - Never commit .vault_password_file to git
# - Use strong, unique passwords
# - Rotate passwords regularly
# - Restrict file permissions to owner only (600)
# - Store password securely in production (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault)

your-secure-vault-password-change-this
